data.title: ..Dee, John - The Private Diary of Dr. John Dee
data.meta_description:
..Dee, John - The Private Diary of Dr. John Dee - Free download as PDF File (.pdf), Text File (.txt) or read online for free. Dr. John Dee's diary provides concise summaries of key events from 1577:
1) Several important Elizabethan figures, including the Earl of Leicester and Philip Sidney, visited Dee's home in January 1577. 
2) Dee hired a barber to maintain his hedges and gardens and began printing his work Hexameron Britannicum in August 1577.
3) Dee had financial difficulties in June 1577, borrowing money from several lenders and pawning a gold chain.
